<%- include('../partials/header') %>

<div class="row g-4">
  <div class="col-lg-8 mx-auto">
    <nav aria-label="breadcrumb" class="mb-3">
      <ol class="breadcrumb"><li class="breadcrumb-item"><a href="/">Home</a></li><li class="breadcrumb-item active">Fact Check Policy</li></ol>
    </nav>

    <div class="card border-0 shadow-sm p-4 p-md-5">
      <div class="d-flex align-items-center gap-3 mb-4">
        <span style="background:var(--gradient);width:48px;height:48px;border-radius:12px;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;flex-shrink:0;">
          <i class="bi bi-patch-check-fill text-white fs-5"></i>
        </span>
        <div>
          <h1 class="h3 fw-bold mb-0">Fact Check Policy</h1>
          <p class="text-muted small mb-0">Last updated: January 2025</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="legal-content">
        <p class="lead">ApolloNews takes the accuracy of information we publish seriously. This policy outlines our approach to verification and our stance on misinformation.</p>

        <h4 class="fw-bold mt-4">Our Commitment to Accuracy</h4>
        <p>Accuracy is a foundational principle of ApolloNews. We are committed to presenting information that is as accurate as possible and to promptly correcting errors when they occur. No financial, political, or commercial consideration will cause us to publish or retain information we know to be false.</p>

        <h4 class="fw-bold mt-4">Aggregated News</h4>
        <p>The majority of content on ApolloNews is aggregated from established news organisations via licensed APIs. We rely on these organisations' own editorial standards and verification processes for the accuracy of their reporting. ApolloNews does not independently verify every claim in third-party articles.</p>
        <p>For this reason, we strongly encourage readers to click through to original source articles and to consult multiple reputable sources before forming conclusions on significant claims, especially in rapidly developing stories.</p>

        <h4 class="fw-bold mt-4">Original Editorial Content</h4>
        <p>For original articles written by our editorial team, our verification standards include:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Claims are traced to primary sources (peer-reviewed research, official government data, court documents, verified press releases)</li>
          <li>Statistics are cross-checked against original datasets where possible</li>
          <li>Direct quotes are verified through recordings, official transcripts, or direct correspondence</li>
          <li>Before publication, articles undergo internal review by at least one senior editor</li>
          <li>For technically complex topics, we seek comment or review from subject-matter experts</li>
        </ul>

        <h4 class="fw-bold mt-4">Misinformation Response</h4>
        <p>If ApolloNews becomes aware that content we have published contains materially false information, we will:</p>
        <ol>
          <li>Immediately remove or clearly label the content pending investigation</li>
          <li>Investigate the origin and extent of the inaccuracy</li>
          <li>Publish a prominent correction in accordance with our <a href="/corrections">Corrections Policy</a></li>
          <li>Where the error was significant, publish an explanatory note describing what was wrong and what the correct information is</li>
        </ol>

        <h4 class="fw-bold mt-4">We Do Not</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>Knowingly publish false or misleading information</li>
          <li>Fabricate quotes, statistics, or events</li>
          <li>Use manipulated images or misleading headlines</li>
          <li>Delete corrections silently — all corrections are documented</li>
        </ul>

        <h4 class="fw-bold mt-4">Reporting Suspected Misinformation</h4>
        <p>If you believe a claim on our Site is factually incorrect, please let us know via our <a href="/contact">Contact page</a>. Include the specific URL, the claim in question, and any supporting evidence. We will investigate within 5 working days.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

